            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-24T09:31:21+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-24T09:31:21+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-24T00:01:21Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-24T00:01:21Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front will stall over central SA today as a low pressure system develops near Kangaroo Island. The low is expected to move north over the Eyre Peninsula early in the week, weakening as it moves into NSW. A trough may linger near the southern coasts before weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA later in the week.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
